  "guide.welcome.title": "Welcome to Prowl!",
  "guide.welcome.body": "Let's take a quick 30-second spin around your new creative playground. You'll know where everything lives in no time.",
  "guide.hierarchy.title": "The Hierarchy",
  "guide.hierarchy.body": "Every object in your scene lives here, nested into a neat little family tree. Click one to select it, drag to reparent, right-click for more.",
  "guide.hierarchy.tip": "Coming from Unreal? This is your World Outliner. In Godot, it's the Scene dock.",
  "guide.scene.title": "The Scene View",
  "guide.scene.body": "This is your canvas. Fly around, move things, and shape your world. Flip to the Game tab any time to see it through the player's eyes.",
  "guide.scene.tip": "Unreal calls this the Viewport; Godot calls it the 2D/3D editor workspace.",
  "guide.inspector.title": "The Inspector",
  "guide.inspector.body": "Select anything and its knobs and dials show up here. Tweak properties, add components, and watch it all update live.",
  "guide.inspector.tip": "This is Unreal's Details panel, and (handily) Godot's Inspector too.",
  "guide.project.title": "The Project Browser",
  "guide.project.body": "All your assets, in one tidy place. Drag models, textures and scripts straight into your scene to bring them to life.",
  "guide.project.tip": "Unreal's Content Browser; Godot's FileSystem dock.",
  "guide.console.title": "The Console",
  "guide.console.body": "Your logs, warnings and errors land here. Keep an eye on it - it's the first place to look when something acts up.",
  "guide.console.tip": "Unreal's Output Log; Godot's Output & Debugger panels.",
  "guide.theme.title": "Make It Yours",
  "guide.theme.body": "Last stop! Click this palette any time to recolor and restyle the entire editor. Go on - make Prowl feel like home.",

